The paper proposes a network architecture for generating videos from captions, which involves understanding the semantic meaning of the captions and combining it with the long-term and short-term dependencies between video frames. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves generating videos based on captions, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also involves spatio-temporal style transfer, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the network's ability to perform unsupervised learning and action recognition, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
